raw_data.title: Executive Consultant
raw_data.description: Principal who has final authority in the conduct of engagements and full responsibility for the work performed.  Responsible for directing consulting services in all service lines and provides senior?level executive oversight of all project related activities.  Ensures that all services provided by the firm comply with the Firm’s Quality Standards, applicable professional standards, and the Firm’s overall objectives of professional excellence. Executive also determines the nature, timing, and extent of procedures and ensures compliance with Firm’s policies and professional standards.

raw_data.title: Principal / Sr. Consultant
raw_data.description: Senior manager who has organizational development and project delivery skills. Oversees the most complex, and technically challenging projects. Demonstrates proficiency in chosen service line and a minimum of awareness of all service lines. Identified as an expert go-to person within the firm in the chosen service line. Initiates and conducts lessons learned meetings during each engagement and fosters an environment of continuous improvement. Demonstrates commitment and modeling of the firm's shared values and code of conduct.

raw_data.title: Sr. Project Manager
raw_data.description: Accountable for leading and delivering projects from planning to closeout and effectively balancing the competing demands of quality, scope, time, and cost. Delivers quality results safely, on time, on budget, and in a manner which meets client’s expectations.  Leverages strengths to ensure optimal performance.  Consistently measures progress toward goals by implementing and reviewing relevant measures. Acquires the resources, information and tools to ensure team can perform at top level.  Provides direction and sets expectations and boundaries for appropriate behaviour by project team.  Comfortably confronts and works through conflict, finding common ground and common goals.

raw_data.title: Sr. Professional Engineer
raw_data.description: Expert in the selected field of engineering. Independently applies advanced techniques to complex assignments. Oversees the work of engineering team. Strives to stay abreast of current development in the selected field and drives innovation in design work.

raw_data.title: Sr. Cost/Value Engineer
raw_data.description: Expert in the cost/value engineering. Independently applies advanced techniques to complex assignments. Oversees the work of value engineering teams. Performs independent review of cost estimates.

raw_data.title: Sr. Risk Specialist
raw_data.description: Expert in risk management. Independently applies advanced techniques to complex assignments. In consultation with the project team, identifies project risks, performs qualitative and quantitative risk analysis, and develops risk response and risk mitigation strategies.

raw_data.title: Sr. Cost Estimator/Scheduler
raw_data.description: Expert in the cost estimating for major projects. Certified as Cost Estimating Professional (CEP). Independently applies advanced techniques to complex assignments to develop cost estimates of specified accuracy. Performs independent review of cost estimates. Cost estimator with Associate Value Specialist (AVS) Certification may participate in value engineering review.  Senior Cost Estimators with Planning & Scheduling Professional (PSP) certification handle all scheduling needs of a project.

raw_data.title: Project Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for delivering programs/projects from planning to closeout under the guidance of Senior Project Manager. Carries out the required planning activities with an end goal in mind.  Clearly delegates tasks and supports individual efforts in delivering results. Effectively marshals resources to get things done. Lays out tasks in sufficient detail to provide path forward for others. Maintains focus on key details (deliverables, timelines, stakeholder concerns), even when presented with multiple tasks or challenging situations. Is resourceful and able to foresee and plan around obstacles (including people-based issues).  Communicates progress, challenges, risks, and contingency plans in a timely and appropriate manner to the stakeholders.

raw_data.title: Professional Engineer
raw_data.description: Fully competent professional in all convention aspects of the subject matter.  Provides services under minimal-to-general supervision. Promotes a work environment characterized by innovation, creativity, teamwork, transparency, integrity and respect. Leads design efforts in the assigned work package under general guidance of a Senior Professional Engineer.

raw_data.title: Engineer Intern II
raw_data.description: Responsible for executing the assigned activities in compliance with project plan and applicable specifications within the allocated time under general direction and limited-to-moderate supervision. Monitors, troubleshoots, and reports on project activities and escalates to Professional Engineer or Project Manager as appropriate. Performs engineering calculations, participates in the development of project documents, and performs basic field engineering functions.

raw_data.title: Engineer Intern I
raw_data.description: Entry level positions that follows prescribed procedures and detailed instructions under the direct supervision of a professional engineer. Performs engineering calculations, participates in the development of project documents, and performs basic field engineering functions.

raw_data.title: Sr. Inspector
raw_data.description: Must have in-depth knowledge of several construction trades and essential job functions. Evaluates overall project performance on a regular basis and documents with subsequent reports. Establishes framework to ensure project is meeting quality standards. Responsible for ensuring that the assigned activities are executed in compliance with project plans and applicable specifications.  Plans, organizes, coordinates and supervises the work activities of the quality assurance personnel and provides them the technical and administrative leadership.  Monitors, troubleshoots, and reports on project activities and escalates as appropriate. Promotes a safe work environment.  Ensures that the work is characterized by innovation, creativity, teamwork, transparency, integrity and respect. Performs a variety of personnel management functions such as overseeing attendance, participating in setting performance standards, training, resolving informal complaints, and orienting new employees on projects.

raw_data.title: Inspector
raw_data.description: Must have knowledge of essential job functions. Provides limited supervision for routine tasks and sequential steps at construction sites. Inspects all craft activities at the site and provides support to senior inspector.  Interpret plans and specifications relating to routine construction problems. Resolves differences between plans and specification that do not impact cost or require engineering design.  Requires engineering or supervisory assistance to resolve differences involving complex problems and discrepancies.  Decides on the acceptability of construction methods and practices, workmanship, materials, and the finished product.  Inspection reports are reviewed for accuracy, completeness and adequacy. Escalates unusually difficult issues to the senior inspector.  May also be responsible for routine project safety inspection and supervision of field quality assurance/quality control.

raw_data.title: Sr. Administrative Assistant
raw_data.description: Provides administrative support to the project delivery team. Responsible for delivering high quality documents with help from Administrative Assistant.  Responsible for generating and binding reports, minor research, and assists occasionally on projects when needed. Also, must have basic understanding of management services, strategic planning, budgeting, and statistical support. Must also possess working knowledge of reporting tools and software for the purpose of presenting plans, concepts, strategies, and theories to clients in an efficient manner. Must be able to execute assignments of a complex nature with minimal technical guidance.

raw_data.title: Administrative Assistant
raw_data.description: Primarily responsible for word processing and data entry.  Assists the Associates and Consultants on project tasks. Provides clerical support and receptionist services. Generates and bind reports.  Must possess working knowledge of reporting tools and software for the purpose of presenting plans, concepts, strategies, and theories to clients in an efficient manner. Must be able to execute assignments of a complex nature with guidance from Senior Administrative Assistant or other members of the project team.
